            <p>MOSES SMITH&#44;<lb/>
                208 WASHINGTON ST&#44;<lb/>
                BROOKLYN&#44; N. Y.<lb/>
                Jan 30&#45;&#45;88<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev &#38; Dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>Please pardon me for sending to you&#44; unauthorized&#44; a copy of my<lb/> book&#58; &#34;Plain Truths About Stock Speculation.&#34;&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Successful in business and mortgage investments in the country over<lb/> 30 years.  Most of my money came in at one time and it was the mistake<lb/> of my life that I took it into speculation.  Money gone and physically weak&#44;<lb/> I saw no opening for a living except to write a book from my experience<lb/> in &#34;the street.&#34;  Publishers and middlemen want about all the profits&#44; hence<lb/> I publish and sell myself to get the benefits.  A long illness interfered<lb/> with selling the books and for expenses I had to draw on money laid by<lb/> towards paying the debt incurred in publishing them.  My family was<lb/> broken up last spring wife is with a friend in the country yet&#44; while I<lb/> am here in a top floor room at &#36;1.25. a week rent&#44; boarding myself<lb/> and working daily until 10 P. M. trying to get a little start and<lb/> have a home again&#44; even with the odds of deafness&#44; age and poor health<lb/> against me.<lb/></p>
            <p>If you are not pleased to buy the copy I send you&#44; I inclose 4c. in<lb/> stamps for return postage on book&#44; but if you&#44; or some friend&#44; are pleased<lb/> to buy it&#44; please return the 2 stamps as the books cost me 35<hi rend="sup">&#162;</hi> each<lb/> for the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1000 copies&#44; including electrotyping.&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Very Respectfully<lb/> Moses Smith<lb/></p>
            <p>Please see Testimonials.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
